Print summary of excellent discriminants analysis

Source: R/excellent_discriminants.R
print_excellent_summary.Rd

Displays a comprehensive summary of the excellent discriminants found in the analysis, including count, score ranges, test performance, parameter ranges, and usage recommendations.

Usage

print_excellent_summary(
  results_file = "discriminant_analysis_results/raw_results.rds"
)

Arguments

results_file

Path to the analysis results RDS file (default: "discriminant_analysis_results/raw_results.rds")

Value

NULL (invisibly). Function is called for its side effect of printing a formatted summary to the console.

Details

The summary includes:

  • Total count of excellent discriminants

  • Overall score range

  • Test performance summary (pass rates for each test type)

  • Parameter ranges (min/max for a, b, c, and discriminant)

  • Top 5 discriminants by score

  • Usage recommendations with example function calls

Note

This function is primarily for interactive use to quickly assess the results of discriminant analysis.

See also

load_excellent_discriminants, get_recommended_discriminants

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Print summary of excellent discriminants
print_excellent_summary()

# Print summary from custom results file
print_excellent_summary("my_analysis/results.rds")
} # }
